node.text:
My favorite way to style my hair and doesn’t take more than 10 minutes! Simply use a 1.5 in barrel (I’ve taken the clamp off an old curler) and curl random pieces to create a beach like texture. 

Super video conference friendly as it can help you look put together. You can focus on pieces more towards your face, if you’re super strapped for time! 

I use:
+ a T3 1.5 in wand 
+ Texturizing spray by Kristen Ess
+ Hairspray by Davines

Been trying super hard to have a consistent skincare routine that’s easy to follow and works with my sensitive skin. 

Products used: 
+biossance marine algae eye cream

node.text:
Fourth day of school and things are finally starting to click ✨ 

Personally these first few days were tough. Not because of the kids, but because of me as an educator. I forgot how much energy it takes to constantly be “on”. 

Throw in learning a brand new school,new curriculum, new students and a whole new bell schedule and I’m impressed I’ve managed to do as well as I have. 🤣

It’s important in these moments to give yourself grace. If you’re a new teacher or in a new position or even at a new school don’t set your personal expectations too high. 

I went in expecting myself to take off where I left off a year ago when we had to leave suddenly March 23, 2020. However you can’t do that to yourself. 

Just as our students are relearning what it’s like to be in school and be a student. We are relearning how to be a teacher. The energy you need. The time it takes to prep things. The multitasking. The planning of pacing lessons. 

Give yourself a little grace and I promise it does all come back. ✨

node.text:
Big news ✨

Traded in my 45 min commute for a 12 min one. After some tough decisions I decided to switch to a school much closer to home. When I say tough decision, I mean it. Glendora was my home for 4 marvelous years, but after having a baby I knew it was time to find something closer. I am so happy where I landed and feel so welcome already. Tustin unified is where I will be calling my new home and I cannot wait to see what this adventure holds. 

I am excited that I will be staying in fifth, moving classrooms was a feat, hence why I have been MIA, but I’m hoping to give y’all a tour soon.

node.text:
Just trying to live up my last weeks of summer you know? ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Not long ago I was the teacher who always said “teaching is my life”. It was my “hobby” and I loved every minute of it. I’ve soon learned how unhealthy that is. The reason being that if you make your career your everything. Who are you when it’s not your career any more? ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Working those insane hours doesn’t make you a better teacher. I would get there first and stay so late. Creating and making my classroom the best. Staying up late making a fun resource to use. But in reality what was I doing for myself? ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
When having a baby I was worried I wouldn’t be able to do all the fun things anymore. Instead you learn to prioritize. I spend my weekends and nights with my family. I still will take some time to create for my classroom, but it’s on a much more healthy scale. I still do the fun lessons in my class, but I’m more choosy on what’s going to benefit everyone the most. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Balance is hard, but at the end of the day, you and your family are the most important. At the end of your life are you going to be so happy you stayed at work until 7pm or are you going to remember the amazing vacation you went on or crazy milestone one of your kids hit. It’s this point on the year when everyone is talking about going back that I like to remind you of how important that balance is. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Don’t get caught up in the hype just because you see it on Instagram.

node.text:
If I’m honest I’m having a tough time getting things for my classroom this year because I have no clue what’s going to be allowed and what’s not. 

However, the off chance that this year or next we are allowed to use shared supplies I snagged these fun acrylic lazy Susan bins. If I can’t use them for tables I know they could easily be used to many ways. Creative writing station, organizing my desk, storing snacks. 🤣

Found in the @target dollar section for $5 each 

How would you use these in your class?

node.text:
Sharing a side to me today that maybe not many of you know, but I’ve been struggling lately and wanted to share a few things in case there are others out there feeling the same. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I can get pretty bad body dysmorphia. I know it stems 100% from being a dancer especially in ballet.  You’re told to suck in your stomach, wear only tights and a leotard and are smack dab in front of a mirror. It’s impossible not to judge yourself. Because of that, have HATED wearing shorts since I was a little girl because I despise how my legs look. I’m a binge eater. Love a good cocktail/wine. Never will say no to a good dessert. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Becoming a mom comes with so many gifts, but it also has its challenges. Your changing body is one thing and comments from others does not help one bit. I have heard stories of people asking postpartum moms when they’re due, if they’ve lost the baby weight yet or even talking about how we look post baby. I know none of these are meant with Ill intent but man does it kill you to hear these things when your emotions are already on a roller coaster. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I’m currently working on feeling confident with myself again, and wow I forgot how hard it is. My mom always talked so negatively about her body and I know that affected me in so many ways. I am vowing to never do that as I don’t want Lyla to go through the same things and feel the way about herself that I ever did. Working on being body positive. Making more positive eating habits, and always being supportive of myself and her. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
And I know it’s a super small victory. But I went out in public the other day in bike shorts. Now I did have on a large sweatshirt, but we’re taking baby steps. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
But just wanted to say especially if you’re a new mom or mom. I feel you. You’re not alone. ✨
